HEADWORD: Culls
<hw>Culls</hw> <pr>(k?lz)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[From Cull,,
<pos>v. t.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Refuse timber, from which the
best part has been culled out.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Any refuse stuff, as rolls not properly
baked.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cully</ent>⟦br⟧
